project_descr: EU-UNDP Low-Carbon Products Certification Project in Guangdong and Chongqing

outputs.output_descr:
The EU-UNDP Low Emission Capacity Building Programme was launched in Jan 2011 as a collaborative but country-driven project that aimed to strengthen technical and institutional capacities at the country level and facilitate inclusion and coordination of the public and private sector in national climate change. 

The outcomes of the project are 
1) Low carbon product certification implementation rules developed for Chongqing and Guangdong, 
2) Low carbon product standards and GHG accounting  methodologies for motorcycle and wrought aluminum alloy, 
3) Low carbon product certification pilots and
